Package elfarol

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Agent
    An interface representing an agent in the El Farol Bar model.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AgentAverage
    Agent which predicts attendance by averaging it's current memory
    AgentMarkov
    Agent that predicts bar attendance using a Markov Chain, mapping previous attendance to expected attendance.
    AgentRan
    An agent that predicts attendance by picking a random number between the highest and lowest attendance values that it remembers.
    AgentWeighted
    Defines an agent of the El Farol simulation.
    ElFarolContextBuilder
    The context builder for the El Farol simulation.
    History
    A simple utility class that is designed to handle the history (i.e., the attendance level of the previous 2 * memorySize week).
    ParameterWrapper
    A simple wrapper class that handles the parameters and their values specified for the simulation.
    Utils
    Simple wrapper class for common utility methods for the El Farol simulation.
